Here's a step-by-step guide to setting up a new React project and rendering "Hello World" using Create React App (CRA):

Step 1: Initialize a new React project using CRA
Open your terminal and run the following command:

```
bash
npx create-react-app hello-world
```

This will create a new React project in a folder called "hello-world".

Step 2: Navigate to the project folder
Run the following command:

```
bash
cd hello-world
```

Step 3: Review the project structure
The project structure should follow best practices:

```
bash
hello-world/
  node_modules/
  public/
  src/
    App.css
    App.js
    App.test.js
    index.css
    index.js
    logo.svg
    reportWebVitals.js
    setupTests.js
  .gitignore
  package.json
  README.md
```

Step 4: Modify the main component (App.js) to display "Hello World"
Open the `src/App.js` file and replace the existing code with the following:

```
jsx
import React from 'react';

function App() {
  return (
    <div className="App">
      <h1>Hello World!</h1>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```
